com.ibm.jaggr.core

Class InitParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.jaggr.core.InitParams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<InitParams.InitParam>

    public class InitParams
extends Object
implements Iterable<InitParams.InitParam>
    Wrapper class for aggregator init-params.

    Init params are specified with the init-param attribute in the servlet element of the org.eclipse.equinox.http.registry.servlets extension point.

      • SERVICEPROVIDERS_INITPARAM

        public static final String SERVICEPROVIDERS_INITPARAM
        Name of the servlet init-param that specifies the name of the service provider extension(s) used by this servlet. Multiple extensions may be specified using multple init-params. The extensions will be initialized in the order that they are specified.

        Service provider extensions are generally used to register OSGi services such as config variable resolvers, etc.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CONFIG_INITPARAM

        public static final String CONFIG_INITPARAM
        Name of the servlet init-param that specifies the URI to the server side AMD config JSON. If the config JSON resides in the same bundle as the defining servlet, then the config URI may specify a relative path
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • OPTIONS_INITPARAM

        public static final String OPTIONS_INITPARAM
        Name of the servlet init-param that specifies the filename of the java properties file containing the aggregator options (see IOptions). If not specified, then the aggregator will look for options properties in the file aggregator.properties in the home directory of the user that started the aggregator.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RESOURCEID_INITPARAM

        public static final String RESOURCEID_INITPARAM
        Name of the servlet init-param that specifies resource ids. Resource ids are used to specify resource alias and base-name values using init-param names of the form :alias and :base-name. For example, the following init-params would specify a resource with alias foo and base-name foopath: 
         <init-param name="resource-id" value="foores"/>
 <init-param name="foores:alias" value="foo"/>
 <init-param name="foores:base-name" value="foopath"/>
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
